Project 02 - Windows Failed Login Detection (Brute Force Monitoring)
Objective
To monitor and alert on unauthorized login attempts (Event ID 4625) using Wazuh SIEM to detect potential brute-force activities on a Windows endpoint.

Lab Environment
Wazuh Server

Windows 10/11 Endpoint

Wazuh Agent

Windows Security Event Logs

Tasks Performed
Configured Audit Policy: Modified Windows Local Security Policy to enable "Audit Logon Events" (Failure).

Log Integration: Ensured Wazuh Agent is successfully forwarding Windows Security logs to the Wazuh Manager.

Threat Simulation: Performed intentional failed login attempts (Event ID 4625) to trigger security events.

Detection & Analysis: Filtered logs in the Wazuh Discover dashboard to isolate and verify the authentication failure events.

Results
Successfully captured and visualized multiple failed login attempts.

Verified that the SIEM correctly identifies and logs authentication failures in real-time.

The monitoring pipeline is confirmed to be operational for detecting suspicious authentication patterns.

Conclusion: 
Successfully configured and tested a detection mechanism for failed login attempts (Event ID 4625). This lab demonstrates the ability to monitor authentication security and serves as a foundational step for detecting brute-force attacks in an enterprise environment.
